---
description: Rules for generating and editing draw.io .drawio architecture diagrams
globs:
  - "**/*.drawio"
  - "**/*.xml"
alwaysApply: false
---

When creating or editing draw.io files, follow these rules:

## Structural validity

- Preserve valid draw.io mxGraph XML.
- The root must contain:
  - `<mxCell id="0"/>`
  - `<mxCell id="1" parent="0"/>`
- Every cell must have a unique ID.
- Every cell except root cells must have a valid parent.
- Every vertex must include `vertex="1"`.
- Every edge must include `edge="1"`.
- Every edge source and target must reference existing vertex IDs.
- Generate or verify all vertices before edges.
- Every `<mxGeometry>` must include `as="geometry"`.
- Do not use unescaped `&`, `<`, or `>` inside labels.
- Use `&amp;` instead of `&`.
- Use `html=1` if labels contain HTML such as `<br>`.

## Layout rules

- Prefer infinite canvas for documentation-style diagrams:
  - `page="0"`
  - `grid="1"`
  - `gridSize="10"`
- Use readable spacing, alignment, and grouping.
- **Absolute routing rule:** connectors must never pass through the interior of any node/block (white content boxes). Route around blocks using orthogonal waypoints in lane gaps, below/above blocks, or just outside block edges.
- Connectors **may** cross other connectors when unavoidable; crossing block interiors is never allowed.
- Avoid arrows crossing through node text.
- Avoid connector labels overlapping nodes.
- If connector labels clutter the diagram, remove them and use a legend.
- Keep architecture overview diagrams under 18–25 nodes.
- Use larger node text: 14–16 px.
- Use section titles: 18–20 px.
- Use dark text on light boxes.

## Editing existing diagrams

When editing an existing `.drawio` file:
- Preserve the existing pages unless explicitly asked to delete them.
- Preserve existing architecture content unless asked to redesign it.
- Prefer moving, resizing, restyling, and rerouting over regenerating from scratch.
- Validate that the file still opens in draw.io after editing.
